From bab313827d51a8ff6606dc31e01ff939ffd48c47 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 4 Jul 2025 19:05:50 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/9] Upstream:DP:wifi: ath12k: add monitor desc pool support
 by replacing idr

Currently, IDR is used to track the skb shared across the source and
destination rings. IDs allocated through idr_alloc are mapped to the
monitor source ring's cookie and fetched back from the destination ring's
cookie. This solution works optimally for skb-related memory.

As part of host memory optimization, migrate the monitor ring from
traditional skb allocation to page frag memory allocation. Unlike skb_cb,
there is no data structure to store host-related information, making IDR
an inefficient solution.

To address this issue, introduce a monitor descriptor pool where each host
descriptor stores skb-related information such as skb address, physical
address, and additional flags. Also removed unused IDR related data
structures from monitor destination ring path.

Patch-dependency:
0406-0001-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Enable-word-mask-subscriptio.patch

Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
